<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - REMOVE -
        MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two mainshaft rear bearing retainers and remove the snap ring from the groove in
                the rear of the mainshaft. Use caution as this will free the spring-loaded centering ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303092">Figure 92</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303092" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303092" filename="../figg13/g1303092.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 92. Remove Mainshaft Rear Bearing Retainers and Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It may be necessary to relieve pressure on the snap ring by tapping on the front of the
                        mainshaft.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splined retainer from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303093">Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303093" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303093" filename="../figg13/g1303093.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 93. Remove Splined Retainer From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Center the front of the mainshaft in the case bore and remove the centering ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303094">Figure 94</hotlnk>). Remove the six springs from the centering ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303094" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303094" filename="../figg13/g1303094.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 94. Remove Centering Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Keep the mainshaft centered and tap to the rear to expose the mainshaft rear bearing snap
                ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303095">Figure 95</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303095" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303095" filename="../figg13/g1303095.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 95. Expose Mainshaft Rear Bearing Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing from the case with pry bars (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303096">Figure 96</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303096" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303096" filename="../figg13/g1303096.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 96. Remove Bearing From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse gear washer from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303097">Figure 97</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303097" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303097" filename="../figg13/g1303097.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 97. Remove Reverse Gear Washer From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block the right countershaft against the side of the case and move the mainshaft assembly to
                the rear. Tilt the front of the shaft up and lift the assembly from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303098">Figure 98</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303098" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303098" filename="../figg13/g1303098.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 98. Lift Assembly From Case</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The reverse gear is free and can fall from the shaft.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>Remove the reverse gear from the mainshaft.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
